{
  "sourceUrl": "https://doxa.life/resources/tips-for-prayer-champions/",
  "slug": "resources/tips-for-prayer-champions",
  "locale": "en",
  "title": "Tips for Prayer Champions",
  "excerpt": null,
  "meta_description": null,
  "og_image": null,
  "featured_image": null,
  "custom_css": null,
  "body_json": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "1.  Align with Church Leadership First"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before inviting others, bring your pastor or ministry leader into the vision. Share why this people group matters to you — "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "your testimony is more compelling than any promotional material."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Ask for their blessing. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://vimeo.com/1143355099/39f8c1f131?fl=pl&fe=vl",
                  "target": "_blank",
                  "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                  "class": null,
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "DOXA promo video"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a strong starting point if they are unfamiliar with the campaign."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "2.  Work Within Existing Church Rhythms"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You don’t need to build something new."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Bring the vision into what is already alive"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": small groups, prayer nights, missions gatherings, Sunday moments. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/resources/small-group-discussion-guide/",
                  "target": "_blank",
                  "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                  "class": null,
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Group Discussion and Prayer Guide"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in our resource section offers detailed suggestions for embedding this well in a small group setting."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "3.  Cast Vision"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Help people see God’s heart for the unreached and the weight of what it means that an entire people group has never heard. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/resources/talking-points/",
                  "target": "_blank",
                  "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                  "class": null,
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Talking Points for Presenters"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in our resource section has suggestions to help you. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Motivation that lasts comes when people grasp the vision for themselves."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Expect the Spirit to do what you cannot. "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "4.  Begin with Key Influencers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Start with group leaders, spiritually faithful church members, and family and friends within your circle who share God’s heart for the nations. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Personal invitations carry weight that announcements never will."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " You might consider "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://zume.training/relational-stewardship-list-of-100/",
                  "target": "_blank",
                  "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                  "class": null,
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "this Relational Stewardship activity"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to help you identify people you already know. When the right people say yes, others follow. When those people begin inviting alongside you, the movement multiplies beyond what you could have built alone. "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "5.  Keep the On-Ramp Clear and Simple"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A complicated invitation produces hesitation, not commitment. Make it easy for people to say yes:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "explain clearly what participation looks like"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "and keep the QR code or sign-up link readily visible on slides, emails, and flyers."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "6.  Pray When You Invite"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Whenever you can, "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "close the invitation with prayer"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". This is not a technique — it is an acknowledgement that you are not the one doing the convincing. It shifts the moment from recruitment to spiritual partnership and invites the Holy Spirit to do what only He can: soften hearts toward a people He already loves."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "7.  Serve the Church"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Position this campaign as a deepening of what your church already values"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": prayer, missions, obedience. Participation in this campaign is a part of transformative discipleship!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "8.  Share Stories That Resonate"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testimonies of prayer, obedience, and global impact stir faith in ways that data cannot. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Be attentive to periodic updates and stories from DOXA and bring them to your community"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". A story of what God is doing builds excitement and anticipation.  "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "9.  Follow Up Relationally, Not Administratively"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Emails and templates are useful — "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/resources/email-templates/",
                  "target": "_blank",
                  "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                  "class": null,
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "customizable versions"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " are available to support you — but they are the floor, not the ceiling. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "A personal check-in, a shared prayer, a brief testimony carries what a reminder cannot."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " People persevere in what they feel personally connected to, not just digitally subscribed to."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "10.  Measure Faithfulness, Not Just Numbers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sign-ups are encouraging, but they are not the fruit. Celebrate obedience, consistency, and spiritual growth. Growth may be steady and quiet rather than immediate and visible. That is the nature of prayer. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Trust that God works deeply through what is faithfully offered,"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " even when the results are not yet yours to see."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              },
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Steward your relationships well, keep God’s heart for the nations before your people, and trust the Holy Spirit to do what you cannot."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "textAlign": null
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
